  Mrs Cotton was a  friend of <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="COT01">Mary Wollstonecraft's </persName>.  Wollstonecraft stayed with her in Berkshire when she was recovering from her break-up with Imlay.
  Mrs Cotton visited Wollstonecraft in London when she and Godwin first became intimate.   It is unclear whether there was a Mr Cotton, and we cannot be certain that 
  Godwin's entries for 'M Cotton'  relate to Mrs Cotton. As a result they have not been coded. Plain 'Cotton' entries after 1797 have not been coded.
